
== '''''GSTQ'' ==
'''
Pronunciation: (gee-sss-teê-qü)
1. Old English salutation (c.1609)
2. Used today in academic circles to display
an affinity to the English monarchy
3. An acronym for "'''G'''od '''S'''ave '''T'''he '''Q'''ueen" 

Examples:
''
When saying goodbye...''

"Well, I'm off. Pip pip, cheerio. '''GSTQ'''."''

When saying hello...''

Person 1: "GSTQ, Craig"

Person 2: "GSTQ, Tom"